stimate)\n! style=\"width:20%;\"| Location\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Date\n! style=\"width:20%;\"| Event\n! style=\"width:20%;\"| Disease\n! style=\"width:5%;\"| Ref.\n|-\n|\n| [[Congo Basin]]\n| 1896\u20131906\n|\n| [[Trypanosomiasis]]\n| <ref>[http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs259/en/ African trypanosomiasis] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161204153318/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs259/en/ |date=2016-12-04 }}, [[World Health Organization]]</ref>\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"800,000\"| >&nbsp;800,000\n| [[Europe]], [[Asia]], [[Africa]]\n| 1899\u20131923\n| [[Sixth cholera pandemic]]\n| [[Cholera]]\n| <ref name=Hays2005 />\n|-\n| 113\n| [[San Francisco plague of 1900\u20131904|San Francisco]]\n| 1900\u20131904\n| \n| [[Bubonic plague]]\n| <ref>{{Cite book |title=Plague Ports: The Global Urban Impact of Bubonic Plague: 1894\u20131901 |last=Echenberg |first=Myron |publisher=New York University Press |year=2007 |isbn=978-0-8147-2232-9 |location=Sacramento |page=231}}</ref>\n|-\n|\n| [[Uganda]]\n| 1900\u20131920\n|\n| [[Trypanosomiasis]]\n| <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1G1-115694306.html |title=Reanalyzing the 1900\u20131920 sleeping sickness epidemic in Uganda |access-date=2008-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090916025017/http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1G1-115694306.html |archive-date=2009-09-16 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n|\n| [[Egypt]]\n| 1902\n|\n| [[Cholera]]\n| <ref name=Kuhnke /><ref name=Gallagher />\n|-\n| 22\n| [[India]]\n| 1903\n|\n| [[Plague (disease)|Bubonic Plague]]\n| <ref name=\"DSHS\" />\n|-\n|4\n|[[Fremantle]]\n|1903\n|\n|[[Bubonic plague]]\n|<ref>{{cite wikisource |title=Report on the outbreak of plague at Fremantle |date=1903 |first1=George Hugh Spencer |last1=Blackburne |first2=T. L. |last2=Anderson}}</ref>\n|-\n| 40,000\n| [[China]]\n| 1910\u20131912\n| 1910 China plague\n| [[Bubonic plague]]\n| <ref name=\"Harbin Plague\" />\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"1,500,000\"| 1,500,0