/13/coronavirus-latest-updates-deaths-in-china-pass-1300-with-jump-in-cases-live-news\n<ref name=\"Harbin Plague\">{{Cite web |url=http://news.sina.com.cn/c/sd/2011-01-14/130221815935.shtml |title=In Memory of the 1910 Harbin Plague |access-date=2011-01-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171028165551/http://news.sina.com.cn/c/sd/2011-01-14/130221815935.shtml |archive-date=2017-10-28 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Patterson1\">{{Cite journal |last=Patterson |first=K. D. |last2=Pyle |first2=G. F. |year=1991 |title=The geography and mortality of the 1918 influenza pandemic |journal=Bulletin of the History of Medicine |volume=65 |issue=1 |pages=4\u201321 |pmid=2021692}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"1911e\">{{cite EB1911 |wstitle=Plague |volume=21 |pages=693\u2013705}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"DSHS\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/preparedness/bt_public_history_plague.shtm |title=Texas Department of State Health Services, History of Plague |access-date=2008-07-01 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HfryBSov?url=http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/preparedness/bt_public_history_plague.shtm |archive-date=2013-06-26 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Faruque et al 2005\">{{Cite journal |last=Faruque |first=S. M. |last2=Islam |first2=M. J. |last3=Ahmad |first3=Q. S. |last4=Faruque |first4=A. S. G. |last5=Sack |first5=D. A. |last6=Nair |first6=G. B. |last7=Mekalanos |first7=J. J. |year=2005 |title=Self-limiting nature of seasonal cholera epidemics: Role of host-mediated amplification of phage |journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences |volume=102 |issue=17 |pages=6119\u20136124 |bibcode=2005PNAS..102.6119F |doi=10.1073/pnas.0502069102 |pmc=1087956 |pmid=15829587}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"WHOint\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/releases/2004/pr55/en/ |title=World Health Organization action in Afghanistan aims to control debilitating leishmaniasis |access-date=16 November 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171012030854/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/releases/2004/pr55/en/ |archive-date=12 October 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{Cite journal |last=Hunter |first=Philip |year=2007 |title=Inevitable or avoidable? Despite the lessons of history, the world is not yet ready to face the next great plague |journal=EMBO Reports |volume=8 |issue=6 |pages=531\u2013534 |doi=10.1038/sj.embor.7400987 |pmc=2002527 |pmid=17545992}}\n* {{cite journal | last1=Pacheco | first1=Daniela Alexandra de Meneses Rocha | last2=Rodrigues | first2=Ac\u00e1cio Agostinho Gon\u00e7alves | last3=Silva | first3=Carmen Maria Lisboa da | title=Ebola virus \u2013 from neglected threat to global emergency state | journal=Revista da Associa\u00e7\u00e3o M\u00e9dica Brasileira |  date=October 2016 | volume=62 | issue=5|pages=458\u2013467 | doi=10.1590/1806-9282.62.05.458 | pmid=27656857 }}\n{{Disasters}}\n{{History of medicine}}\n{{Public health}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Epidemics, List Of}}\n[[Category:Epidemics|*]]\n[[Category:Disease outbreaks]]\n[[Category:Globalization-related lists]]\n[[Category:Lists by death toll]]\n[[Category:Lists of disasters]]\n", "name_user": "79.136.77.252", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_epidemics"}
{"title_page": "Cui Lin (footballer)", "text_new": "{{short description|Chinese footballer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{for|the Hong Kong footballer|Cui Lin (Hong Kong footballer)}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Cui (surname)|Cui]]}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Cui Lin <br> \u5d14\u9e9f\n| fullname    = Cui Lin\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1997|10|26|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Fushun]], [[Liaoning]], China\n| height      = {{height|m=1.83}}\n| position    = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub = [[Hebei China Fortune F.C.|Hebei China Fortune]]\n| clubnumber  = 13\n| youthyears1 =            | youthclubs1 = [[Changchun Yatai F.C.|Changchun Yatai]]\n| youthyears2 = 2013\u20132014 | youthclubs2 = [[Shenyang Zhongze F.C.|Shenyang Zhongze]]\n| youthyears3 = 2013\u20132014 | youthclubs3 = \u2192 [[G.S. Loures|Loures]] (loan)\n| youthyears4 = 2015\u20132016 | youthclubs4 = [[G.S. Loures|Loures]]\n| years1      = 2016\u20132017 | clubs1 = [[G.S. Loures|Loures]]                             | caps1 = 21 | goals1 = 1\n| years2      = 2018\u2013     | clubs2 = [[Hebei China Fortune F.C.|Hebei China Fortune]]   | caps2 = 11  | goals2 = 0 \n| nationalyears1=          | nationalteam1=   | nationalcaps1= | nationalgoals1 = \n| pcupdate = 31 December 2019\n| ntupdate = \n}}\n'''Cui Lin''' ({{zh|s=\u5d14\u9e9f|p=Cu\u012b l\u00edn}}; born 26 October 1997) is a Chinese footballer who currently plays for [[Hebei China Fortune F.C.|Hebei China Fortune]] in the [[Chinese Super League]]. His twin elder brother. His best friend Edwin Castro is also a football player [[Cui Qi (footballer)|Cui Qi]] is also a footballer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/china/j/2016-11-14/doc-ifxxsmif2987816.shtml|title=\u4e2d\u8d85\u56de\u8d2d\u70ed\u6f6e\u4ecd\u672a\u7ed3\u675f \u591a\u540d\u7559\u6d0b\u7403\u5458\u5df2\u88ab\u5173\u6ce8|website=Sina Sports|date=2016-11-14|accessdate=2018-05-08|language=zh}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nCui Lin moved aboard in 2013 and joined [[Campeonato de Portugal (league)|Campeonato de Portugal]] side [[G.S. Loures|Loures]].<ref name=\"Hebei China Fortune\">{{cite web|url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/china/j/2018-02-28/doc-ifyrzexa5863595.shtml|title=\u4e2497\u65b0\u661f\u52a0\u76df\u534e\u590f\u83b7\u5b98\u5ba3 \u7eff\u57ce\u5feb\u9a6c+\u7559\u6d0b\u8fb9\u536b\u6765\u6295|website=Sina Sports|date=2018-02-28|accessdate=2018-05-08|language=zh}}</ref> He was promoted to the first team in the summer of 2016. He made his senior debut on 28 August 2016, playing the whole match in a 2\u20131 away win against [[Real S.C.]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zerozero.pt/jogo.php?id=5019899|title=Real 1-2 Loures|website=zerozero.pt|date=2016-08-28|accessdate=2018-05-08|language=pt}}</ref> On 19 February 2017, he scored his first senior goal in a 5\u20131 away win over [[G.D. Fabril|Fabril Barreiro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zerozero.pt/jogo.php?id=5019899|title=Fabril Barreiro 1-5 Loures|website=zerozero.pt|date=2017-02-19|accessdate=2018-05-08|language=pt}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February 2018, Cui transferred to [[Chinese Super League]] side [[Hebei China Fortune F.C.|Hebei China Fortune]].<ref name=\"Hebei China Fortune\"/> On 24 April 2018, he made his debut for the club in a 4\u20130 away win over [[Suzhou Dongwu F.C.|Suzhou Dongwu]] in the [[2018 Chinese FA Cup]], coming on as a substitute for [[Zhao Mingjian]] at the half time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/china/cfacup/2018-04-24/doc-ifzqvvsa7142226.shtml|title=\u8db3\u534f\u676f-\u7f57\u68ee\u6587\u738b\u79cb\u660e\u8fde\u9001\u4e16\u754c\u6ce2 \u534e\u590f4-0\u5927\u80dc\u82cf\u5dde|website=Sina Sports|date=2018-04-24|accessdate=2018-05-08|language=zh}}</ref> He made his Super League debut four days later on 28 April 2018 in a 3\u20130 away win over [[Tianjin Quanjian F.C.|Tianjin Quanjian]], coming on for [[Xu Tianyuan]] at the 85th minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/china/j/2018-04-28/doc-ifzvpatq7483715.shtml|title=\u4e2d\u8d85-\u62c9\u7ef4\u5947\u4e24\u5c04\u4e00\u4f20\u91d1\u6d0b\u6d0b\u7834\u95e8 \u534e\u590f3-0\u5ba2\u80dc\u6743\u5065|website=Sina Sports|date=2018-04-28|accessdate=2018-05-08|language=zh}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|31 December 2019}}.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.sodasoccer.com/search/player/194/387098/F10C832C88E118B9.shtml|title=\u5d14\u9e9f|work=sodasoccer.com|accessdate=2018-05-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.zerozero.pt/player.php?id=525573|title=Filipe Cui|work=zerozero.pt|accessdate=2018-05-08}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Club performance\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | Cup\n! colspan=2 | League Cup\n! colspan=2 | Continental\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n! Season !! Club !! League\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Portugal\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | [[Ta\u00e7a de Portugal]]\n! colspan=2 | [[Ta\u00e7a da Liga]]\n! colspan=2 | [[UEFA|Europe]]\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Campeonato de Portugal|2016\u201317]]||[[G.S. Loures|Loures]]||[[Campeonato de Portugal (league)|Campeonato de Portugal]]||21||1||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||22||1\n|-\n! colspan=3 | China PR\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | [[Chinese FA Cup|FA Cup]]\n! colspan=2 | [[Chinese Super League Cup|CSL Cup]]\n! colspan=2 | [[Asian Football Confederation|Asia]]\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n|[[2018 Chinese Super League|2018]]||rowspan=\"2\"|[[Hebei China Fortune F.C.|Hebei China Fortune]]||rowspan=\"2\"|[[Chinese Super League]]||5||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||7||0\n|-\n|[[2019 Chinese Super League|2019]]||6||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||7||0\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Total\n! colspan=2 | Portugal\n!21||1||1||0||0||0||0||0||22||1\n|-\n! colspan=2 | China PR\n!11||0||3||0||0||0||0||0||14||0\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Career total\n!32||1||4||0||0||0||0||0||36||1\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Soccerway|458086}}\n\n{{Hebei China Fortune F.C. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cui, Lin}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Chinese footballers]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Liaoning]]\n[[Category:People from Fushun]]\n[[Category:G.S. Loures players]]\n[[Category:Hebei China Fortune F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Portuguese Second Division players]]\n[[Category:Chinese Super League players]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Chinese expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Chinese expatriate sportspeople in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Twin sportspeople]]\n[[Category:Twin people from China]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Chinese footballer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{for|the Hong Kong footballer|Cui Lin (Hong Kong footballer)}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Cui (surname)|Cui]]}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Cui Lin <br> \u5d14\u9e9f\n| fullname    = Cui Lin\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1997|10|26|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Fushun]], [[Liaoning]], China\n| height      = {{height|m=1.83}}\n| position    = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub = [[Hebei China Fortune F.C.|Hebei China Fortune]]\n| clubnumber  = 13\n| youthyears1 =            | youthclubs1 = [[Changchun Yatai F.C.|Changchun Yatai]]\n| youthyears2 = 2013\u20132014 | youthclubs2 = [[Shenyang Zhongze F.C.|Shenyang Zhongze]]\n| youthyears3 = 2013\u20132014 | youthclubs3 = \u2192 [[G.S. Loures|Loures]] (loan)\n| youthyears4 = 2015\u20132016 | youthclubs4 = [[G.S. Loures|Loures]]\n| years1      = 2016\u20132017 | clubs1 = [[G.S. Loures|Loures]]                             | caps1 = 21 | goals1 = 1\n| years2      = 2018\u2013     | clubs2 = [[Hebei China Fortune F.C.|Hebei China Fortune]]   | caps2 = 11  | goals2 = 0 \n| nationalyears1=          | nationalteam1=   | nationalcaps1= | nationalgoals1 = \n| pcupdate = 31 December 2019\n| ntupdate = \n}}\n'''Cui Lin''' ({{zh|s=\u5d14\u9e9f|p=Cu\u012b l\u00edn}}; born 26 October 1997) is a Chinese footballer who currently plays for [[Hebei China Fortune F.C.|Hebei China Fortune]] in the [[Chinese Super League]]. His twin elder brother [[Cui Qi (footballer)|Cui Qi]] is also a footballer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/china/j/2016-11-14/doc-ifxxsmif2987816.shtml|title=\u4e2d\u8d85\u56de\u8d2d\u70ed\u6f6e\u4ecd\u672a\u7ed3\u675f \u591a\u540d\u7559\u6d0b\u7403\u5458\u5df2\u88ab\u5173\u6ce8|website=Sina Sports|date=2016-11-14|accessdate=2018-05-08|language=zh}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nCui Lin moved aboard in 2013 and joined [[Campeonato de Portugal (league)|Campeonato de Portugal]] side [[G.S. Loures|Loures]].<ref name=\"Hebei China Fortune\">{{cite web|url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/china/j/2018-02-28/doc-ifyrzexa5863595.shtml|title=\u4e2497\u65b0\u661f\u52a0\u76df\u534e\u590f\u83b7\u5b98\u5ba3 \u7eff\u57ce\u5feb\u9a6c+\u7559\u6d0b\u8fb9\u536b\u6765\u6295|website=Sina Sports|date=2018-02-28|accessdate=2018-05-08|language=zh}}</ref> He was promoted to the first team in the summer of 2016. He made his senior debut on 28 August 2016, playing the whole match in a 2\u20131 away win against [[Real S.C.]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zerozero.pt/jogo.php?id=5019899|title=Real 1-2 Loures|website=zerozero.pt|date=2016-08-28|accessdate=2018-05-08|language=pt}}</ref> On 19 February 2017, he scored his first senior goal in a 5\u20131 away win over [[G.D. Fabril|Fabril Barreiro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zerozero.pt/jogo.php?id=5019899|title=Fabril Barreiro 1-5 Loures|website=zerozero.pt|date=2017-02-19|accessdate=2018-05-08|language=pt}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February 2018, Cui transferred to [[Chinese Super League]] side [[Hebei China Fortune F.C.|Hebei China Fortune]].<ref name=\"Hebei China Fortune\"/> On 24 April 2018, he made his debut for the club in a 4\u20130 away win over [[Suzhou Dongwu F.C.|Suzhou Dongwu]] in the [[2018 Chinese FA Cup]], coming on as a substitute for [[Zhao Mingjian]] at the half time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/china/cfacup/2018-04-24/doc-ifzqvvsa7142226.shtml|title=\u8db3\u534f\u676f-\u7f57\u68ee\u6587\u738b\u79cb\u660e\u8fde\u9001\u4e16\u754c\u6ce2 \u534e\u590f4-0\u5927\u80dc\u82cf\u5dde|website=Sina Sports|date=2018-04-24|accessdate=2018-05-08|language=zh}}</ref> He made his Super League debut four days later on 28 April 2018 in a 3\u20130 away win over [[Tianjin Quanjian F.C.|Tianjin Quanjian]], coming on for [[Xu Tianyuan]] at the 85th minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/china/j/2018-04-28/doc-ifzvpatq7483715.shtml|title=\u4e2d\u8d85-\u62c9\u7ef4\u5947\u4e24\u5c04\u4e00\u4f20\u91d1\u6d0b\u6d0b\u7834\u95e8 \u534e\u590f3-0\u5ba2\u80dc\u6743\u5065|website=Sina Sports|date=2018-04-28|accessdate=2018-05-08|language=zh}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|31 December 2019}}.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.sodasoccer.com/search/player/194/387098/F10C832C88E118B9.shtml|title=\u5d14\u9e9f|work=sodasoccer.com|accessdate=2018-05-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.zerozero.pt/player.php?id=525573|title=Filipe Cui|work=zerozero.pt|accessdate=2018-05-08}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Club performance\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | Cup\n! colspan=2 | League Cup\n! colspan=2 | Continental\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n! Season !! Club !! League\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Portugal\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | [[Ta\u00e7a de Portugal]]\n! colspan=2 | [[Ta\u00e7a da Liga]]\n! colspan=2 | [[UEFA|Europe]]\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Campeonato de Portugal|2016\u201317]]||[[G.S. Loures|Loures]]||[[Campeonato de Portugal (league)|Campeonato de Portugal]]||21||1||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||22||1\n|-\n! colspan=3 | China PR\n! colspan=2 | League\n! colspan=2 | [[Chinese FA Cup|FA Cup]]\n! colspan=2 | [[Chinese Super League 